article.headline: Brown 78, Pennsylvania 74
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Jason Forte scored 29 points and Mike Martin hit two crucial free throws with 11 seconds left as Brown held off a furious Penn rally and defeated the Quakers 78-74 Friday. Pat Powers had 22 points and six steals for Brown (11-11, 7-2 Ivy), which made 28 of 52 shots (53.8 percent) in the game. Mark Zoller had a career-high 24 points, and Adam Chubb added 21 for Penn (12-9, 5-3), which had a five-game winning streak snapped. Brown took a 71-56 lead on a 3-point shot by Powers with 6:10 remaining. Jeff Schiffner then hit a 3-point shot starting a 14-2 Quaker run, and Penn pulled to within 73-71 on two foul shots by Chubb with 1:11 remaining. Two free throws by Forte gave Brown a 76-73 edge with 29 seconds to go, and after Zoller made one of two foul shots with 13 seconds remaining, Martin hit his two clinching foul shots. A layup by Penn's Steve Danley gave Penn a 30-28 lead with 3:03 left in the first half, but led by Forte's 16 points, Brown moved out to a 36-34 halftime lead and never trailed again.
